programme.desc: Queensland v New South Wales (Kick-off 11.15am). Coverage of game one of the three-match series, which takes place at Melbourne Cricket Ground. The State of Origin is seen by many as being the pinnacle of the sport, and as such brings a great deal of prestige to the players who are selected to represent the Australian state in which they played their first senior rugby league game. Queensland have been the dominant force in this competition since the turn of the Millennium, and have won 11 of the last 12 series dating back to 2006.(n)
